Section 1:
1 L.D. 1639
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 647, L.D. 1639, “An Act to Codify
10 Minimum Instructional Hours in the State's Schools”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Education to Conduct a Statewide Survey
13 Related to Instructional Time in Public Schools'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Statewide survey; instructional time. Resolved: That the Department
16 of Education shall conduct a statewide survey of school administrative units to collect data
17 on the number of hours a day used for instructional time in schools throughout the State.
18 No later than December 1, 2025, the department shall submit a report with the results of
19 the survey to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs. The
20 committee may report out a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
21 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
22 appropriations and allocations are made.
23 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
24 School Finance and Operations Z078
25 Initiative: Provides one-time funds for a part-time contracted position to administer the
26 statewide survey on the number of hours a day used for instructional time in schools and
27 analyze the results.
28 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
29 All Other $30,000 $0
30 __________ __________
31 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $30,000 $0
3228 '
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR2139(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 647, L.D. 1639
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. It also adds an appropriations and
33 allocations section. The amendment directs the Department of Education to conduct a
44 statewide survey of school administrative units to collect data on the number of hours a day
55 used for instructional time in schools. The department is required to submit a report with
66 the results of the survey to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs
77 by December 1, 2025.
88 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
99 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR2139(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
