1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. It also adds an appropriations and
33 allocations section. The amendment directs the Department of Education to conduct a
44 statewide survey of school administrative units to collect data on the number of hours a day
55 used for instructional time in schools. The department is required to submit a report with
66 the results of the survey to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs
77 by December 1, 2025.
